lead_paragraph: A sailor who sent out a distress signal during a storm in the Gulf of California was found safe aboard his boat and was continuing his voyage, the Coast Guard said on Friday. A Coast Guard jet and a Mexican Navy ship located George Van Sickle and his dog aboard his 17-foot sailboat on Thursday afternoon, officials said at the Coast Guard's 11th District headquarters.
